# pt-BR locale (not pt-PT)

**Audience:** Operators and prospects in **Brazil** first; **English** remains the global lingua franca for paths, commits, APIs, and many technical terms.

**Operator chat:** When the operator writes in Portuguese, replies follow the **same** vocabulary and style bar — see **`.cursor/rules/operator-chat-language-pt-br.mdc`** (always applied) and **`.cursor/skills/operator-dialogue-pt-br/SKILL.md`**.

## Prefer (pt-BR) vs avoid (typical pt-PT)

| Prefer | Avoid |
|--------|--------|
| arquivo | ficheiro |
| compartilhar / compartilhamento | partilhar / partilha |
| seção | secção |
| ações (if needed) | acções |
| usuário | utilizador |
| atualizar | actualizar |
| artefato(s) | artefacto(s) |
| assinatura (SaaS / licença) | subscrição |
| acessa / acessam | acede / acedem |
| console (DevTools, UI) | consola |
| equipe | equipa |
| precisa / tem que / deve (obligation) | tem de |
| continua usando / continua precisando | continua a usar / continua a precisar |
| falhando (not “X a falhar”) | … a falhar |
| gerenciador de senhas | gestor de senhas (optional; BR often uses gerenciador) |

Keep **English** for commands, product names, and jargon where the repo already does (e.g. `docker prune`, **Bitwarden**, **Teams**).

## Automation

- Run **`uv run pytest tests/test_docs_pt_br_locale.py -v`** after large doc edits. The scan includes **`docs/private/**/*.pt_BR.md`** when present (not gitignored from pytest’s point of view), same idea as markdown lint for local operator trees.
- Extend **`tests/test_docs_pt_br_locale.py`** (`_extra_locale_scan_paths`) if **`docs/private/pitch/slides.yaml`** or website copy becomes tracked and includes pt-BR strings.

